title: Best Bites: Crunchy taco cups
text:
Welcome to Best Bites, a twice-weekly video series that aims to satisfy your never-ending craving for food content through quick, beautiful videos for the at-home foodie. Check back on Tuesdays and Thursdays for new episodes! 
Ingredients 24 wonton wrappers 1 lb lean ground beef 1 packet taco seasoning 1 can tomatoes 1 1/2 cup cheddar cheese, shredded Directions In a pan, heat oil. Brown beef. Add in taco seasoning. Add in tomatoes. Stir, stir, stir. Place wonton wrappers in a muffin pan. Add beef filling and cheese. Add another layer of wonton wrapper, beef and cheese. Bake at 375 degrees for 11-13 minutes. Garnish. Enjoy! Read more...
